title: Royal Bank of Canada’s Earnings Top Estimates - WSJ
text:
Royal Bank of Canada, the country’s largest lender by assets, reported fiscal third-quarter results Wednesday that beat expectations and raised its quarterly dividend by 3%.
Toronto-based RBC said it had a net profit of 2.48 billion Canadian dollars ($1.86 billion), or C$1.66 a share, in the quarter ended July 31, up from C$2.38 billion, or C$1.59 a share, a year earlier.
